{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.3",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 3 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:1",
      "text": "After this, Job opened his mouth, and cursed his day,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:2",
      "text": "And he said:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:3",
      "text": "Let the day perish wherein I was born, and the night in which it was said: A man child is conceived.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:4",
      "text": "Let that day be turned into darkness, let not God regard it from above, and let not the light shine upon it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:5",
      "text": "Let darkness, and the shadow of death, cover it, let a mist overspread it, and let it be wrapped up in bitterness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:6",
      "text": "Let a darksome whirlwind seize upon that night, let it not be counted in the days of the year, nor numbered in the months.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:7",
      "text": "Let that night be solitary, and not worthy of praise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:8",
      "text": "Let them curse it who curse the day, who are ready to raise up a leviathan:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:9",
      "text": "Let the stars be darkened with the mist thereof: let it expect light, and not see it, nor the rising of the dawning of the day:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:10",
      "text": "Because it shut not up the doors of the womb that bore me, nor took away evils from my eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:11",
      "text": "Why did I not die in the womb? why did I not perish when I came out of the belly?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:12",
      "text": "Why received upon the knees? why suckled at the breasts?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:13",
      "text": "For now I should have been asleep and still, and should have rest in my sleep:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:14",
      "text": "With kings and consuls of the earth, who build themselves solitudes:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:15",
      "text": "Or with princes, that possess gold, and fill their houses with silver:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:16",
      "text": "Or as a hidden untimely birth, I should not be; or as they that, being conceived, have not seen the light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:17",
      "text": "There the wicked cease from tumult, and there the wearied in strength are at rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:18",
      "text": "And they sometime bound together without disquiet, have not heard the voice of the oppressor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:19",
      "text": "The small and great are there, and the servant is free from his master.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:20",
      "text": "Why is light given to him that is in misery, and life to them that are in bitterness of soul?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:21",
      "text": "That look for death, and it cometh not, as they that dig for a treasure:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:22",
      "text": "And they rejoice exceedingly when they have found the grave?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:23",
      "text": "To a man whose way is hidden, and God hath surrounded him with darkness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:24",
      "text": "Before I eat I sigh: and as overflowing waters, so is my roaring:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:25",
      "text": "For the fear which I feared, hath come upon me: and that which I was afraid of, hath befallen me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.3.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:26",
      "text": "Have I not dissembled? have I not kept silence? have I not been quiet? and indignation is come upon me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
